<subSubSection id="C3326E8AFFF8C10E7FE2FD66FC7CF2C5" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF8C10E7FE2FD66FC7CF2C5" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1173]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FE2FD66FDF1F4BE" box="[189,616,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
Comment:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E11FD66FDF1F4BE" box="[334,616,724,750]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">Glossadelphus falcatulus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was published in 1929 as an endemic species to 
<collectingCountry id="F33F7D91FFF8C10E7BD3FD66FB56F4BE" box="[1164,1231,724,750]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7B81FD66FA06F4BF" author="Brotherus, V. F." box="[1246,1439,724,751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref7859" refString="Brotherus, V. F. (1929 b) Symbolae Sinicae 4. Musci. Julius Springer, pp. 1 - 147." type="book chapter" year="1929">Brotherus 1929b</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7F91FD45FEFBF541" author="Tixier, P." box="[206,354,759,785]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="319 - 356" refId="ref9667" refString="Tixier, P. (1988) Le genre Glossadelphus Fleisch. (Sematophyllaceae, Musci) et sa valeur. Nova Hedwigia 46: 319 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">Tixier (1988)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7DD6FD45FBFBF542" authority="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityName="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityYear="1939" box="[649,1122,759,786]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="kerstanii">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7DD6FD45FC3BF541" box="[649,930,759,785]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Ectropothecium kerstanii</emphasis>
Dixon &amp; Herzog
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7BDCFD4AFAC9F542" author="Herzog, T." box="[1155,1360,759,786]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="71 - 97" refId="ref8590" refString="Herzog, T. (1939) Zwei Bryophytensammlungen aus dem Sikkimhimalaya. Annales Bryologici 12: 71 - 97." type="journal article" year="1939">Herzog (1939: 96)</bibRefCitation>
without any comments. Our examination of 
<typeStatus id="549383A3FFF8C10E7D42FCA9FDD4F565" box="[541,589,795,821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">type</typeStatus>
materials of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7DBEFCA9FCEBF564" box="[737,882,794,821]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7DBEFCA9FCEBF564" box="[737,882,794,821]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. falcatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7CF5FCA9FBB2F564" authorityName="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityYear="1939" box="[938,1067,794,820]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="kerstanii">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7CF5FCA9FBB2F564" box="[938,1067,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. kerstanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that both species should be placed into 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E74FC8FFE44F507" authorityName="Mitten" authorityYear="1868" box="[299,477,829,855]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7E74FC8FFE44F507" box="[299,477,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
just as 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7D6EFC8FFD40F508" author="Tixier, P." box="[561,729,829,856]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="319 - 356" refId="ref9667" refString="Tixier, P. (1988) Le genre Glossadelphus Fleisch. (Sematophyllaceae, Musci) et sa valeur. Nova Hedwigia 46: 319 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">Tixier’s (1988)</bibRefCitation>
treatment on them. However, evident morphological differences between the two species are observed. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7D82FCD3FCC6F52B" authorityName="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityYear="1939" box="[733,863,865,891]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="kerstanii">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7D82FCD3FCC6F52B" box="[733,863,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. kerstanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a robust plant with very densely arranged leaves, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7F90FC36FEF9F5CE" box="[207,352,900,926]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7F90FC36FEF9F5CE" box="[207,352,900,926]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. falcatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium-sized plant with slightly loosely arranged leaves. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7B97FC36FAC3F5CE" box="[1224,1370,900,926]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7B97FC36FAC3F5CE" box="[1224,1370,900,926]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. falcatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7F96FC1AFED4F591" authorityName="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityYear="1939" box="[201,333,935,961]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="kerstanii">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7F96FC1AFED4F591" box="[201,333,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. kerstanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in smaller leaves (0.8–1.1 × 
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF8C10E7DF8FC15FCA8F592" box="[679,817,935,962]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
vs. 1.5–1.7 × 
<quantity id="4CD090E4FFF8C10E7C81FC15FBF4F592" box="[990,1133,935,962]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.8">0.8–0.9 mm</quantity>
), triangle dorsal leaves (vs. broadly ovate), oblong-lanceolate lateral leaves (vs. wide lanceolate), and alar regions slightly differentiated, with less than five short rectangular cells (vs. alar regions clearly differentiated, with 10–15 sub-square cells). In conclusion, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7ACFFC5CFF6FF27B" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7ACFFC5CFF6FF27B" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. falcatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E70FBA3FE28F27B" authorityName="Dixon &amp; Herzog" authorityYear="1939" box="[303,433,1041,1067]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="kerstanii">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7E70FBA3FE28F27B" box="[303,433,1041,1067]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. kerstanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent two different independent species. Here, we propose to treat 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7B87FBA3FAF0F27B" box="[1240,1385,1041,1067]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7B87FBA3FAF0F27B" box="[1240,1385,1041,1067]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. falcatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an independent species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7ED5FB86FDA5F21E" authorityName="Mitten" authorityYear="1868" box="[394,572,1076,1102]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7ED5FB86FDA5F21E" box="[394,572,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and make a new combination, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7CC6FB87FB17F21F" authority="(Broth.)" baseAuthorityName="Broth." box="[921,1166,1076,1103]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulum">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7CC6FB87FBB6F21E" box="[921,1071,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. falcatulum</emphasis>
(Broth.)
</taxonomicName>
Z.-Q. Yi &amp; Y. Jia.Among all Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E54FBE5FD8EF221" box="[267,535,1111,1137]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7E54FBE5FE24F221" box="[267,445,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Ectropothecium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7D7EFBEAFD21F221" box="[545,696,1111,1137]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="falcatulum">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7D7EFBEAFD21F221" box="[545,696,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. falcatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7C6BFBEAFB1CF221" authority="Cardot &amp; Ther." authorityName="Cardot &amp; Ther." box="[820,1157,1111,1137]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Ectropothecium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="ohosimense">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7C6BFBEAFC4CF221" box="[820,981,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">E. ohosimense</emphasis>
Cardot &amp; Thér.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7BF9FBE5FA18F222" author="Theriot, M. H. I." box="[1190,1409,1111,1138]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="250 - 254" refId="ref9594" refString="Theriot, M. H. I. (1908) Diagnoses d'especes et de varietes nouvelles de mousses. Bulletin de l'Academie Internationale de Geographie Botanique 18: 250 - 254." type="journal article" year="1908">Thériot (1908: 251)</bibRefCitation>
but the latter is different in having denser and shorter branches and shorter setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
